s are highly telecentric in design,  delivering a bright, sharp image across the entire frame, with excellent  color and contrast.','<p>The HDx Optical Adapter turns the B4 lens into a longer focal length  lens, so that the relative depth of field expected for the larger sensor  is achieved, while the usual field of view when the lens is mounted to a  2/3 camera is maintained.<br /><br />&#13;\nAll HDx Optical Adapters also optically correct for the different  spectral alignments between three-chip prism block sensors, for which  the B4-mount lenses were designed, and the single sensor of the large  sensor cameras. HDx Optical Adapters are highly telecentric in design,  delivering a bright, sharp image across the entire frame, with excellent  color and contrast.</p>',1,NULL,17,0,'','250','700','1350',228,'Lenses and Accessories','Lens Mount Adapters',0),(229,'Allows EOSstyle lenses to be mounted on Micro Four-Thirds camera bodies<br />','<p>Allows EOSstyle lenses to be mounted on Micro Four-Thirds camera bodies<br /></p>',1,NULL,17,0,'','25','75','225',229,'Lenses and Accessories','Lens Mount Adapters',0),(230,'Adapts Nikon mount lenses to be used with Micro 4/3rds mount bodies. Includes Iris Ring allowing for iris control on lenses that lack an iris ring. <br /><br />&#13;\rNOTE: Lenses which have a manual iris ring when mounted with this adapter must be mounted with Adapters iris ring set to O. Once mounted move the adapter\'s iris control from the O to o position. Otherwise full iris range won\'t be accessible via the lenses iris control.<br />','<p>Adapts Nikon mount lenses to be used with Micro 4/3rds mount bodies. Includes Iris Ring allowing for iris control on lenses that lack an iris ring. <br /><br />&#13;\nNOTE: Lenses which have a manual iris ring when mounted with this adapter must be mounted with Adapters iris ring set to O. Once mounted move the adapter\'s iris control from the O to o position. Otherwise full iris range won\'t be accessible via the lenses iris control.<br /></p>',1,NULL,17,0,'','25','75','225',230,'Lenses and Accessories','Lens Mount Adapters',0),(231,'Allows PLmount Lenses to be mounted to cameras with Micro 4/3rds lens mounts. Attached support bracket accepts 1/4\"-20 or 3/8\"-16 threaded bolts.<br />','<p>Allows PLmount Lenses to be mounted to cameras with Micro 4/3rds lens mounts. Attached support bracket accepts 1/4\"-20 or 3/8\"-16 threaded bolts.<br /></p>',1,NULL,17,0,'','25','75','225',231,'Lenses and Accessories','Lens Mount Adapters',0),(232,'<div id=\"prodtab1\" style=\"display: block;\">&#13;\r<p><strong>EX 0.75X Aspheric Wide Converter</strong></p>&#13;\r<p>16x9 Inc. introduces the EX 0.75 Aspheric Wide Converter<strong>the first wide converter to bring the benefits of aspheric technology to DV and HDV cameras.</strong> The top-quality optical solution for getting wider angle images from Sony\'s popular new PMW-EX1 and EX3 camcorders, <strong>the EX 0.75X provides a 25% greater angle of view while maintaining full zoom capability.</strong></p>&#13;\r<p><strong>Aspheric Technology<br /></strong>The  EX 0.75\'s innovative, advanced technical design employs a  state-of-the-art aspheric lens element to more effectively reduce  geometric distortion and chromatic aberrations and improve off-axis wide  angle performance. Utilization of the aspheric lens surface allows the  other elements of the converter to be smaller and lighterwithout it,  the spheric elements would have to be larger to achieve the same level  of performance. This helps keep the unit\'s size and weight at a minimum,  making it especially well suited for handheld work. The EX 0.75X  contains a total of four multi-coated optical glass elementsincluding  the asphere lensthat combine to yield clean and vivid, high definition  images.</p>&#13;\r<p><strong>Bayonet Mount<br /></strong>This lightweight,  compact optical accessory attaches securely to the front of the EX1 and  EX3 via a convenient bayonet mount. Installation and 